{"name":"Climb","type":"ability","img":"modules/hyperborea-content/assets/icons/ability.png","system":{"description":"<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 37\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 39\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<p>To ascend or descend sheer cliffs or walls without need of climbing gear, if lightly armoured or unarmoured, as a thief of equal level (see <strong>Table 16</strong>). Chance-in-twelve reduced by 4 if wearing medium <span style=\"font-family: var(--font-primary); font-size: var(--font-size-14);\">armour; impossible in heavy armour. If vertical, the surface must be rough or cracked. At least one check must be made per 100 feet of climbing. Failure indicates the climber has slipped and fallen at about the midpoint of the check.</span></p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<p>[<strong>Table 16: Progressive Thief Abilities</strong> -- see <strong>Player's Manual</strong>, p.37]</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>","autoTags":[],"manualTags":[],"save":"","pattern":"transparent","requirements":"berserker","roll":"d12","rollType":"below","rollTarget":8,"blindroll":false,"tags":[]},"effects":[],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.AN1G3Ad3GIBcAO7j"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"hyperborea","systemVersion":"1.000","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1679253059188,"modifiedTime":1681579168412,"lastModifiedBy":"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea"},"_id":"0noSc6dzJvfPcHV1","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea":3}}
{"name":"Extraordinary Str and Con","type":"ability","img":"modules/hyperborea-content/assets/icons/ability.png","system":{"description":"<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 27\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 43\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<p>+8% chance to perform <em>extraordinary feats of strength</em> and <em>constitution</em> (see <strong>Chapter 3: Statistics</strong>, <em>strength</em> and <em>constitution</em>).</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>","autoTags":[],"manualTags":[],"save":"","pattern":"transparent","requirements":"berserker","roll":"d100","rollType":"below","rollTarget":8,"blindroll":false,"tags":[]},"effects":[],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.YIplOKcVwiJ20PGF"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"hyperborea","systemVersion":"1.000","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1679249969686,"modifiedTime":1681579168413,"lastModifiedBy":"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea"},"_id":"4vaX85B6nGCBtewz","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea":3}}
{"name":"Melee Expert","type":"ability","img":"modules/hyperborea-content/assets/icons/ability.png","system":{"description":"<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 28\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 41\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 44\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<p>At 7th level, a berserker&rsquo;s standard melee attack rate improves from 1/1 to 3/2. Note that weapon mastery can further increase attack rate.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>","autoTags":[],"manualTags":[],"save":"","pattern":"transparent","requirements":"berserker 7","roll":"","rollType":"result","rollTarget":0,"blindroll":false,"tags":[]},"effects":[],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.UbQiMVdAegqnmdRv"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"hyperborea","systemVersion":"1.000","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1679250510524,"modifiedTime":1681579168413,"lastModifiedBy":"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea"},"_id":"5qjC2ZYg4FpjlLoP","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea":3}}
{"name":"Weapon Mastery","type":"ability","img":"modules/hyperborea-content/assets/icons/ability.png","system":{"description":"<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 28\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 41\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<p><em>Mastery</em> of one weapon (+1 &ldquo;to hit&rdquo; and +1 damage). Additional weapons may be mastered at 4th, 8th, and 12th levels. As noted in <strong>Chapter 6: Equipment</strong>, the attack rate for melee weapons and the rates of fire for most missile weapons improve through weapon mastery. <span style=\"font-family: var(--font-primary); font-size: var(--font-size-14);\">N.B.: Unless hunting, berserkers shun the mastery of missile launching weapons. </span>For more information on weapon mastery, see <strong>Chapter 9: Combat</strong>, <em>weapon skill</em>.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>","autoTags":[],"manualTags":[],"save":"","pattern":"transparent","requirements":"berserker","roll":"","rollType":"result","rollTarget":0,"blindroll":false,"tags":[]},"effects":[],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.K1OLRl8YTN53zIp4"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"hyperborea","systemVersion":"1.000","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1679250294860,"modifiedTime":1681579168413,"lastModifiedBy":"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea"},"_id":"EC5SK9HxUAcqrAZP","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea":3}}
{"name":"Hardy","type":"ability","img":"modules/hyperborea-content/assets/icons/ability.png","system":{"description":"<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 40\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<p>Physical resilience and an indomitable will to prevail; +2 bonus to all saving throws.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>","autoTags":[],"manualTags":[],"save":"","pattern":"transparent","requirements":"berserker","roll":"","rollType":"result","rollTarget":0,"blindroll":false,"tags":[]},"effects":[],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.T8VdjzWDNBWfyZ8S"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"hyperborea","systemVersion":"1.000","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1679252841676,"modifiedTime":1681579168413,"lastModifiedBy":"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea"},"_id":"XjONrBXWptG0bMTs","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea":3}}
{"name":"Bestial Form","type":"ability","img":"modules/hyperborea-content/assets/icons/ability.png","system":{"description":"<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 43\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<p>At 7th level, the berserker is blessed by a deity or spirit (animal or ancestral) with the ability to transmogrify into a semi-human, bipedal shape whilst in <em>berserk rage</em>. The <em>bestial form</em> assumed is one typically associ<span style=\"font-family: var(--font-primary); font-size: var(--font-size-14);\">ated with the berserker&rsquo;s culture or ancestry. Once an animal type is selected, it cannot be changed. Choices include bear, lion, tiger, or wolf. During transformation, thews bristle with fur, and countenances elongate to whiskered muzzles. The berserker&rsquo;s hands become paw-like, with great claws or talons. The following benefits apply:</span></p>\n<ul>\n<li><span style=\"font-family: var(--font-primary); font-size: var(--font-size-14);\"><strong>Enlargement:</strong> &times;1.5 height and &times;2 weight</span></li>\n<li><strong>Recovery:</strong> Half of any lost hit points are recovered (does not include false hp total from hit point burst).</li>\n<li><strong>Melee Weapon Use:</strong> Can wield melee weapons and attack as normal.</li>\n<li><strong>Bestial Attack:</strong> Can opt to claw/claw/bite for a base 1d6/1d6/1d8 damage. If both claw attacks strike a single opponent of Small or Medium size, the berserker can hug the victim automatically for an additional 2d6 hp damage. Note that +2 bonuses to attack and damage rolls still apply, per the <em>enhanced combat</em> benefit of <em>berserk rage</em>, as well as strength attack modifier and damage adjustment.</li>\n</ul>\n<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 44\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 44\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<p>The following restrictions apply:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Limited Usage:</strong> Bestial form ends when berserk rage ends.</li>\n<li><strong>Armour:</strong> No armour allowed; indeed, the transformation rips clothes.</li>\n<li><strong>Rage Connexion:</strong> All benefits and detriments associated with berserk rage remain.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>","autoTags":[],"manualTags":[],"save":"","pattern":"transparent","requirements":"berserker 7","roll":"","rollType":"result","rollTarget":0,"blindroll":false,"tags":[]},"effects":[],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.T8VdjzWDNBWfyZ8S"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"hyperborea","systemVersion":"1.000","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1679252841676,"modifiedTime":1681579168412,"lastModifiedBy":"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea"},"_id":"aUTwBc0Gaed3Tynw","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea":3}}
{"name":"Berserk Rage","type":"ability","img":"modules/hyperborea-content/assets/icons/ability.png","system":{"description":"<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 42\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<p>A furious battle lust and feral madness unleashed. A rage may be entered any time during battle; though it is most often witnessed when the berserker&rsquo;s blood has been drawn.</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Frequency of Berserk Rage:</strong>\n<ul>\n<li>1st to 4th levels = &times;1 per day</li>\n<li>5th to 8th levels = &times;2 per day</li>\n<li>9th to 12th levels = &times;3 per day</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li><strong>Duration of Berserk Rage:</strong>\n<ul>\n<li>Rounds equal to the berserker&rsquo;s constitution score.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p>The following benefits and drawbacks apply:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Berserk Attack Rate:</strong> Melee attack rate of 2/1 (or 5/2 with weapon mastery).</li>\n<li><strong>Enhanced Combat:</strong> +2 &ldquo;to hit&rdquo; and damage on all melee attacks.</li>\n<li><strong>Fire Immunity:</strong> Impervious to normal fire; saves vs. magical fire always successful.</li>\n<li><strong>Frightening Aspect:</strong> Fearsome to behold; enemy morale checks at &minus;2 penalty.</li>\n<li><strong>Hit Point Burst:</strong> Temporary hit points equal to one-half of constitution score, rounded up. These false hit points are deducted first whenever the berserker is hit. At the conclusion of the rage, any remaining bonus hit points are subtracted.</li>\n<li><strong>Refusal to Fall:</strong> Can fight to as low as &minus;3 hp. Once the battle is over, the berserker collapses.</li>\n<li><strong>Refusal to Surrender:</strong> Cannot yield, retreat, or withdraw from melee once the <em>rage</em> is begun; neither can the berserker take actions unrelated to battle and bloodshed.</li>\n<li><strong>Unbreakable Willpower:</strong> Immunity to <em>fear</em>, <em>charm</em>, and like sorcery that may affect the berserker&rsquo;s resolve (cf. <em>emotion</em>).</li>\n<li><strong>Uncontrollable:</strong> Once all enemy combatants have been vanquished, the berserker continues to attack or rend slain enemy forms until the <em>rage</em> duration ends. However, on a 1-in-8 chance, the berserker continues attacking any living creature within 30 feet&mdash;including allies&mdash;for 1d6 rounds, before all good sense is regained.</li>\n<li><strong>Exhaustion:</strong> When the rage ends, the berserker is exhausted for 1d3 turns (10&ndash;30 minutes). During this period of lethargy, the berserker suffers a &minus;2 &ldquo;to hit&rdquo; and damage rolls, attack rate is reduced to one attack per round (regardless of level or <em>mastery</em>), and running is impossible. The exhausted berserker is withdrawn and languid.</li>\n<li style=\"list-style-type: none;\">&nbsp;</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>","autoTags":[],"manualTags":[],"save":"","pattern":"transparent","requirements":"berserker","roll":"","rollType":"result","rollTarget":0,"blindroll":false,"tags":[]},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"systemId":"hyperborea","systemVersion":"1.000","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1679255366179,"modifiedTime":1681579168412,"lastModifiedBy":"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea"},"_id":"hubh0v4FMW5iaStS","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea":3}}
{"name":"Leap","type":"ability","img":"modules/hyperborea-content/assets/icons/ability.png","system":{"description":"<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 40\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<p>Mighty thews enable leaps of 25 feet or greater (if unencumbered), bridging pits, chasms, and the like. Vertical leaps of up to 5 feet can also be accomplished.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>","autoTags":[],"manualTags":[],"save":"","pattern":"transparent","requirements":"berserker","roll":"","rollType":"result","rollTarget":0,"blindroll":false,"tags":[]},"effects":[],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.T8VdjzWDNBWfyZ8S"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"hyperborea","systemVersion":"1.000","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1679252841676,"modifiedTime":1681579168413,"lastModifiedBy":"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea"},"_id":"kxKHwV9EMOpiak7B","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea":3}}
{"name":"Thick Skin","type":"ability","img":"modules/hyperborea-content/assets/icons/ability.png","system":{"description":"<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 43\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<p>Flesh not unlike the hide of a bull, which toughens over time. The berserker has natural AC 8 at 1st level, AC 7 at 3rd level, and so on (see <strong>Table 20</strong>). Body armour does not &ldquo;stack&rdquo; with this ability, but <em>thick skin</em> does provide a +1 AC bonus (from 1st to 6th levels) or +2 AC bonus (from 7th to 12th levels) to berserkers clad in light armour. Also, the berserker can function in subfreezing temperatures (as low as &minus;15&deg;F) with little need of protection (e.g., light furs/skins).</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>","autoTags":[],"manualTags":[],"save":"","pattern":"transparent","requirements":"berserker","roll":"","rollType":"result","rollTarget":0,"blindroll":false,"tags":[]},"effects":[],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.T8VdjzWDNBWfyZ8S"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"hyperborea","systemVersion":"1.000","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1679252841676,"modifiedTime":1681579168413,"lastModifiedBy":"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea"},"_id":"sfdXAUfGfLX2TUmz","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea":3}}
